def fmt(x, pos):
    """The two args are the value and tick position"""
    
    return f'{int(x/60/60):,}'+':'+str(int((x/60)%60))+' Hrs'

formatter = FuncFormatter(fmt)

Layouts. CoinIn per Asset¶

Layouts with more assets are naturally bound to make more in total. Lets normalize a layout's sum by the number of assets in it.

In [1013]:
def get_n_machines(layout):
    layout = layout.replace('x','-')
    if '-' not in layout:
        layout='1-'+layout
    width = layout.split('-')[0]
    depth = layout.split('-')[1]
    
    dct={'tri':3,'square':4,'oct':8}
    
    if not depth.isnumeric():
        depth = dct[depth]
    
    return int(depth) * int(width)
